    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen both virtual_lines and vim.lsp.inlay_hint.enable() are enabled, lines are drawn in the wrong position\n\n<img width=\"1258\" height=\"277\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/93f42e2a-f2cd-4997-9984-0496ad977e21\" />\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nIf the code is long, it may be in the correct position when drawn on the first screen, and then scrolling the screen to the rest of the code reveals that the subsequent renders are in the incorrect position, and the line doesn't take into account the position of the inlayhint\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nlike this, this is when this code is displayed correctly when the first screen is drawn\n<img width=\"1297\" height=\"303\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/f8cb15a7-9a17-4333-9afc-198ef34b9759\" />\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.11.3\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\ninconclusive\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOs\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty 0.41.1 created by Kovid Goyal\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\ni dont know\n\n### Installation\n\nhomebrew",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "NONE",
            "body": "Wanna add to this, that this also happens when toggling `inlay_hint` with `virtual_lines` enabled, even with no horizontal scrolling involved. Would be great if toggling `inlay_hint` somehow forced `virtual_lines` to update.\n\nNormally, when using `virtual_lines` they line up horizontally with what they point to.\n<img width=\"1919\" height=\"326\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/c6a29c8f-db2c-4572-9cc8-0f24366896ca\" />\n\nThis also works, when enabling `inlay_hint`\n\n<img width=\"1919\" height=\"301\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/7bb21c17-0dd3-4dd7-a2a1-66a1b293273a\" />\n\nBut either when toggling `inlay_hint` or when `inlay_hint` update on their own, then `virtual_lines` don't point in the correct place horizontally anymore:\n\n<img width=\"1912\" height=\"323\" alt=\"Image\" src=\"https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/12cc190f-d2a8-43fd-95ae-50cd3e2f75de\" />\n\nI toggle both often and at least for the toggling `inlay_hint` case solved this with this dirty timing hack:\n```lua\nvim.keymap.set('n', '<leader>i', function()\n\tlocal bufnr = args.buf\n\tvim.lsp.inlay_hint.enable(not vim.lsp.inlay_hint.is_enabled({ bufnr = bufnr }), { bufnr = bufnr })\n\tvim.defer_fn(function() vim.diagnostic.show(nil, bufnr) end, 50)\nend, opts)\n```",
            "created_at": "2026-03-20T09:05:24Z",
